headline_main: Boris Johnson, Democratic Party, North Korea: Your Wednesday Briefing

abstract: The candidates sparred angrily over whether to wipe out private health insurance and institute a government-run health system.
snippet: The candidates sparred angrily over whether to wipe out private health insurance and institute a government-run health system.
lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — It took only one question — the very first — in Tuesday night’s Democratic presidential primary debate to make it clear that the issue that united the party in last year’s congressional elections in many ways now divides it.

abstract: The 77-year-old democratic socialist from Vermont made clear that he could still own the Democratic debate. And the debate stage.
snippet: The 77-year-old democratic socialist from Vermont made clear that he could still own the Democratic debate. And the debate stage.
lead_paragraph: Bernie Sanders was at it again — center stage, his baritone building to something — right hand raised and restless, as if he were scribbling his words on an invisible chalkboard.

abstract: Ms. Warren has proposed a $1.25 trillion plan that would wipe out most student debt.
snippet: Ms. Warren has proposed a $1.25 trillion plan that would wipe out most student debt.
lead_paragraph: Senator Elizabeth Warren of Massachusetts has structured her presidential campaign around a series of disruptive policy ideas. One of her biggest involves reshaping higher education by canceling most student loan debt and eliminating tuition at public colleges.

headline_main: Elizabeth Warren on Free College and Canceling Student Debt

abstract: Ms. Warren wants to tax the 75,000 wealthiest families in the United States and reduce inequality.
snippet: Ms. Warren wants to tax the 75,000 wealthiest families in the United States and reduce inequality.
lead_paragraph: By now, Senator Elizabeth Warren of Massachusetts is known for being the candidate ready with a plan. But back in January, she was just getting her campaign started. And one of her very first proposals was to impose a wealth tax.

abstract: President Trump said a group of congresswomen should “go back” to the countries they came from — remarks Democrats roundly condemned as racist and divisive.
snippet: President Trump said a group of congresswomen should “go back” to the countries they came from — remarks Democrats roundly condemned as racist and divisive.
lead_paragraph: Earlier this month, President Trump hurled ugly insults at a group of four Democratic congresswomen of color, saying they hated America and that they should “go back” to the countries they came from, despite the fact that all are United States citizens and all but one was born in the country.

abstract: Moderate underdogs kicked off the Detroit debates by targeting the top candidates with charges of “wish-list economics” and “impossible promises” on health care.
snippet: Moderate underdogs kicked off the Detroit debates by targeting the top candidates with charges of “wish-list economics” and “impossible promises” on health care.
lead_paragraph: DETROIT — The leading liberals in the Democratic presidential primary, Senators Bernie Sanders and Elizabeth Warren, strenuously fought back on Tuesday against accusations of making fanciful promises and imperiling the party’s prospects against President Trump, as a group of moderate underdogs sought to slow their momentum in the second round of debates.
